Have you written up cases
like this before?

504
00:37:20,070 --> 00:37:22,026
A few of them for <i>Esquire,</i> yeah.

505
00:37:22,270 --> 00:37:23,498
What do you think?

506
00:37:23,750 --> 00:37:24,978
What do I think?

507
00:37:25,430 --> 00:37:28,467
If you're worried about the D.A.
Grand juries read papers.

508
00:37:28,710 --> 00:37:30,985
Proper spin control
could make a big difference.

509
00:37:31,230 --> 00:37:33,061
What the hell are you talking about?

510
00:37:33,310 --> 00:37:36,108
You said Hanson was a street hustler.
Did he have a record?

511
00:37:36,350 --> 00:37:38,147
Take drugs?
Deal drugs? Pimp?

512
00:37:38,390 --> 00:37:40,620
That kind of spin
can influence a grand jury.

513
00:37:40,870 --> 00:37:42,508
Get investigators to hit the streets.

514
00:37:42,750 --> 00:37:45,423
Every P.I. In town's an off-duty cop.

515
00:37:45,950 --> 00:37:48,589
Besides, why would we need a P. I...

516
00:37:48,830 --> 00:37:51,947
...when we got ourselves
a hotshot New York writer...

517
00:37:52,190 --> 00:37:53,942
...filling all the gaps?

518
00:37:56,310 --> 00:37:57,629
Take care, bubba.

519
00:38:17,590 --> 00:38:19,581
- Are you the flower man?
- No, I'm John Kelso.

520
00:38:19,830 --> 00:38:22,060
Good morning, I'm a writer
and wanted to ask you...

521
00:38:22,310 --> 00:38:24,699
If you're not the flower man,
leave me be.

522
00:38:24,950 --> 00:38:28,704
The Lady's in mourning, and
I haven't received a flower or a rose...

523
00:38:28,950 --> 00:38:31,862
...or anything to show for it.
Please leave me be.

524
00:38:35,350 --> 00:38:39,184
I know Billy Hanson used to live here.
I wanted to ask a few questions.

525
00:38:39,430 --> 00:38:42,103
And if it's an inappropriate time,
I'll come back later.

526
00:38:42,350 --> 00:38:47,026
I can't believe you're running around
ringing my doorbell. Where you from?

527
00:38:47,350 --> 00:38:49,022
Where are your manners?

528
00:38:49,270 --> 00:38:51,022
Just leave me be.

529
00:38:53,750 --> 00:38:55,866
My condolences.
I'll call...

530
00:38:56,630 --> 00:38:58,860
I'll come back another time, or...

531
00:40:22,710 --> 00:40:25,099
I apologize for the delay.

532
00:40:26,870 --> 00:40:31,580
Why, thank you. They're lovely.
They're absolutely lovely.

533
00:40:31,830 --> 00:40:34,549
I'd love to ask you a few questions,
if you have a minute.

534
00:40:35,030 --> 00:40:36,748
Is this your car?

535
00:40:38,710 --> 00:40:40,268
How about a ride home?

536
00:40:44,270 --> 00:40:45,385
Thank you.

537
00:40:54,030 --> 00:40:57,102
What I want to know is,
what is a white boy like you...

538
00:40:57,350 --> 00:41:01,662
...doing driving a big old brother's
jive-ass heap like this shit here?

539
00:41:01,910 --> 00:41:05,061
I just bought this.
I kind of like it. It's not a bad car.

540
00:41:05,310 --> 00:41:07,904
No, it's not bad.
Did I hurt your feelings?

541
00:41:08,150 --> 00:41:10,744
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to hurt your feelings.

542
00:41:10,990 --> 00:41:14,300
I can't help it.
I just call things out as I see it.

543
00:41:14,550 --> 00:41:16,427
I just can't help it.
I just do that.

544
00:41:16,910 --> 00:41:19,344
- One thing you needn't worry about.
- What's that?

545
00:41:19,590 --> 00:41:23,139
Ain't nobody going to try
to steal this piece of shit.

546
00:41:23,790 --> 00:41:27,100
I'm just practicing up till I can save
enough money to get my Rolls.

547
00:41:27,350 --> 00:41:30,148
Chablis is a pretty name.
It's unusual.

548
00:41:30,390 --> 00:41:34,463
Thank you. I got it off a wine bottle.
It's a show name.

549
00:41:34,710 --> 00:41:38,419
- You're an actress?
- I'm not an actress. I'm a showgirl.

550
00:41:38,670 --> 00:41:41,104
I work at the Pick-Up on Congress.

551
00:41:41,350 --> 00:41:45,025
I lip-synch, I emcee, I dance.
You know, shit like that.

552
00:41:45,270 --> 00:41:49,024
The person you see now
is just little old simple Chablis.

553
00:41:49,270 --> 00:41:50,589
But in the evenings...

554
00:41:50,830 --> 00:41:54,061
...when I put on my gowns
and my makeup...

555
00:41:54,310 --> 00:41:56,904
...and my jewelry and my perfume...

556
00:41:57,150 --> 00:41:59,300
...I become "The Lady chablis."

557
00:42:01,710 --> 00:42:04,065
You are just so cute.

558
00:42:04,310 --> 00:42:06,585
A cool white wine for a cool black girl.

559
00:42:06,830 --> 00:42:09,867
And you're full of flattery too.

560
00:42:10,670 --> 00:42:15,027
It's getting hot up in here, honey.
My shots are kicking in.

561
00:42:16,550 --> 00:42:17,460
Excuse me?

562
00:42:17,710 --> 00:42:20,224
Yes, honey, my shots.
Never mind that.

563
00:42:20,470 --> 00:42:22,540
What'd you want to talk to me about?

564
00:42:24,070 --> 00:42:25,185
Billy Hanson.

565
00:42:27,110 --> 00:42:30,705
No. Billy's dead.
Case closed.

566
00:42:31,310 --> 00:42:32,709
Was he your boyfriend?

567
00:42:32,950 --> 00:42:34,463
Billy, my boyfriend?

568
00:42:34,710 --> 00:42:36,109
Were you two lovers?

569
00:42:36,910 --> 00:42:38,138
No. Hell, no.

570
00:42:38,390 --> 00:42:41,188
Billy was way too trashy for me, honey.
I'm a lady.

571
00:42:41,430 --> 00:42:44,069
However, he did date
my roommate Corinne for a while.

572
00:42:45,590 --> 00:42:49,219
The two of those
had some wild times together.

573
00:42:53,270 --> 00:42:56,580
- Those are beautiful.
- So, tell me more about Corinne.

574
00:42:57,310 --> 00:42:59,585
Corinne's like a lot of girls.

575
00:43:00,190 --> 00:43:03,421
She found herself attracted
to the wrong type of man.

576
00:43:04,230 --> 00:43:07,939
Billy was not the right type of man.
She thought she could change him.

577
00:43:08,190 --> 00:43:11,387
But there was no way of changing
that evil son of a bitch.

578
00:43:11,630 --> 00:43:14,098
- I'd love to speak to corinne.
- I'd like to too.

579
00:43:14,350 --> 00:43:18,423
But she skipped town
owing me two months' rent.

580
00:43:18,670 --> 00:43:21,503
And Billy said he would pay for it,
but now he's...

581
00:43:24,030 --> 00:43:25,668
But you know...

582
00:43:25,910 --> 00:43:27,980
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

583
00:43:28,230 --> 00:43:30,949
But you know,
it's like my mama always said...

584
00:43:33,030 --> 00:43:34,986
..."Two tears in a bucket...

585
00:43:35,230 --> 00:43:37,346
...motherfuck it."

586
00:43:38,670 --> 00:43:40,023
I have to remember that one.

587
00:43:40,270 --> 00:43:42,545
Don't remember that one.
That's off-the-record.

588
00:43:50,190 --> 00:43:51,669
Let me get your door for you.

589
00:44:04,790 --> 00:44:06,223
Thank you, hon.

590
00:44:11,990 --> 00:44:15,778
In the phone book,
you were listed as F. De Veau.

591
00:44:17,710 --> 00:44:19,268
What's the "F" stand for?

592
00:44:21,110 --> 00:44:23,499
The "F" stands for Frank, hon.

593
00:44:23,750 --> 00:44:24,978
That's me.

594
00:44:38,990 --> 00:44:40,821
- She's a he.
- Correct.

595
00:44:40,990 --> 00:44:42,264
You're shitting me.

596
00:44:42,510 --> 00:44:45,229
If this thing heats up,
I think you'll want to talk to her.

597
00:44:45,470 --> 00:44:47,301
Proper folks don't discuss such things.

598
00:44:47,750 --> 00:44:49,581
She paints a rotten picture of Billy.

599
00:44:49,830 --> 00:44:52,981
Let me tell you a story.
There was a judge here years ago.

600
00:44:53,230 --> 00:44:56,700
His oldest boy was messing around
with a gangster's girlfriend.

601
00:44:57,670 --> 00:44:59,547
One morning they found him...

602
00:45:00,190 --> 00:45:03,580
...lying under the porch
with his privates tucked into his lapel.

603
00:45:05,950 --> 00:45:07,941
Dead men tell no tales.

604
00:45:08,830 --> 00:45:10,821
Next day, headline read...

605
00:45:11,070 --> 00:45:12,901
..."Fall From Porch Proves Fatal."

606
00:45:14,110 --> 00:45:15,941
Some fall.
What's your point?

607
00:45:16,550 --> 00:45:20,668
Saving face in the light of unpleasant
circumstances is the Savannah way.

608
00:45:22,110 --> 00:45:24,749
I'll try to track down that real girl.
Corinne, you said?

609
00:45:25,350 --> 00:45:27,068
Well, I got to skedaddle.

610
00:45:27,310 --> 00:45:30,268
Doing Christmas at Tybee Island.
We got all sorts of folks coming.

611
00:45:30,510 --> 00:45:31,829
Have a great Christmas.

612
00:45:32,070 --> 00:45:34,425
- You too, John.
- See you later, Uga.

613
00:45:43,270 --> 00:45:45,306
<i>Merry Christmas!</i>

614
00:46:27,510 --> 00:46:29,068
He's got it on a string!

615
00:46:50,990 --> 00:46:52,548
Luther's not eating!

616
00:47:00,630 --> 00:47:01,824
Check, please.

617
00:47:03,150 --> 00:47:04,469
You didn't like it?

618
00:47:04,910 --> 00:47:07,185
No, they were very good.
Excellent.

619
00:47:09,630 --> 00:47:11,029
What was in the vial?

620
00:47:12,630 --> 00:47:15,827
He says it's enough poison
to kill everybody in the county.

621
00:47:17,630 --> 00:47:19,586
If he eats and it's a good day...

622
00:47:19,830 --> 00:47:20,740
...fine.

623
00:47:21,430 --> 00:47:22,545
If he doesn't eat...

624
00:47:22,790 --> 00:47:27,068
...let's put it this way: If I were
you, I wouldn't drink the water today.

625
00:47:27,470 --> 00:47:28,983
Where does he put the poison?

626
00:47:29,230 --> 00:47:31,539
In the water supply system.

627
00:47:33,910 --> 00:47:35,343
Is that true?
Do you believe that?

628
00:47:37,390 --> 00:47:41,781
I've lived here a long time, honey.
I believe most anything about anybody.

629
00:47:45,270 --> 00:47:46,544
Where are we going?

630
00:47:46,790 --> 00:47:48,667
Patience, dear boy.

631
00:47:53,030 --> 00:47:56,909
It's time you meet the most important
member of my defense team.

632
00:47:57,390 --> 00:47:58,789
We're going to the cemetery?

633
00:47:59,030 --> 00:48:02,500
Not Bonaventure.
The colored cemetery's down the road.

634
00:49:03,390 --> 00:49:06,427
Looks like we got the garden
all to ourselves tonight.

635
00:49:09,070 --> 00:49:10,469
Meet Minerva.

636
00:49:13,470 --> 00:49:14,425
How do you do?

637
00:49:16,110 --> 00:49:17,828
You trying to work me, boy?

638
00:49:19,110 --> 00:49:21,180
Put that hand back in your pocket.

639
00:49:28,670 --> 00:49:30,626
I feel sorry for you.

640
00:49:31,430 --> 00:49:33,022
Do tell, Minerva.

641
00:49:33,510 --> 00:49:35,421
He think nobody love him.

642
00:49:38,950 --> 00:49:40,668
That's silly.
We've never met.

643
00:49:43,550 --> 00:49:44,949
You got a hole in you.

644
00:49:45,190 --> 00:49:46,748
Too many questions.

645
00:49:46,990 --> 00:49:51,108
Don't know whether to be this way
or that without the answers.

646
00:49:53,310 --> 00:49:55,870
There ain't no answers.

647
00:50:01,070 --> 00:50:04,346
You come a long way to find that out,
didn't you?

648
00:50:07,310 --> 00:50:10,108
Now we got to get to work.
You bring the money?

649
00:50:12,390 --> 00:50:13,459
Put it on the grave.

650
00:50:15,790 --> 00:50:18,304
Kiss it first,
so it come back to you.

651
00:50:20,670 --> 00:50:22,820
You bring the shiny dimes?

652
00:50:29,870 --> 00:50:30,985
Bury them.

653
00:50:32,110 --> 00:50:35,102
He's working hard against you, James.

654
00:50:35,390 --> 00:50:37,028
Who? Dr. Buzzard?

655
00:50:39,270 --> 00:50:41,306
The boy. The dead boy.

656
00:50:41,830 --> 00:50:43,821
Oh, Billy.
That doesn't surprise us.

657
00:50:44,070 --> 00:50:45,469
Dr. Buzzard?

658
00:50:47,550 --> 00:50:48,983
Ain't got much dead time left.

659
00:50:50,030 --> 00:50:51,224
Dead time?

660
00:50:52,110 --> 00:50:53,668
Lasts an hour.

661
00:50:53,990 --> 00:50:57,221
Half-hour before midnight
till half past.

662
00:50:57,670 --> 00:51:00,548
Half-hour before midnight
for working good.

663
00:51:00,870 --> 00:51:02,940
Half-hour after for evil.

664
00:51:03,190 --> 00:51:05,385
We'll need a little of both tonight.

665
00:51:05,670 --> 00:51:07,262
You got the bottle of water?

666
00:51:09,590 --> 00:51:11,308
Ain't been through no pipe?

667
00:51:12,590 --> 00:51:13,864
Give it to me.

668
00:51:18,630 --> 00:51:20,143
We got to make him...

669
00:51:20,390 --> 00:51:23,302
...Ioosen up on James.

670
00:51:27,030 --> 00:51:28,349
I need Shango...

671
00:51:29,030 --> 00:51:31,100
...and a little <i>hungan.</i>

672
00:51:43,990 --> 00:51:45,025
Come.

673
00:51:46,430 --> 00:51:47,545
Come!

674
00:51:52,510 --> 00:51:54,421
Tell me something about him.

675
00:51:55,230 --> 00:51:56,629
He tried to kill me?

676
00:51:56,870 --> 00:51:59,259
No, before then.
Something good.

677
00:52:01,070 --> 00:52:02,185
Your kind words...

678
00:52:02,430 --> 00:52:04,898
...take root, flower,
come back to bless you.

679
00:52:06,270 --> 00:52:08,101
Something that made him happy?

680
00:52:11,590 --> 00:52:12,705
His Camaro.

681
00:52:13,430 --> 00:52:16,069
He loved his Camaro.
He wouldn't let anyone near it.

682
00:52:16,310 --> 00:52:18,460
That car was his pride and joy.

683
00:52:19,110 --> 00:52:21,305
Keep talking. It's working.
It's working!

684
00:52:22,830 --> 00:52:25,788
He spray painted it flat black.

685
00:52:26,030 --> 00:52:29,306
You should've seen him.
He spent hours on that car, fixing it...

686
00:52:29,550 --> 00:52:30,505
...cleaning it.

687
00:52:30,750 --> 00:52:32,945
He painted racing stripes on it...

688
00:52:33,190 --> 00:52:34,908
...and all kinds of other things.

689
00:52:35,590 --> 00:52:37,023
He was very creative.

690
00:52:39,710 --> 00:52:41,860
That's something
most people didn't know.

691
00:52:42,110 --> 00:52:43,509
He was an artist.

692
00:52:44,270 --> 00:52:46,738
Just now,
when you were saying them things...

693
00:52:46,990 --> 00:52:48,981
...I felt him ease off.

694
00:52:49,790 --> 00:52:51,826
He heard you say you love him.

695
00:52:54,950 --> 00:52:57,464
That's preposterous.
He tried to kill me.

696
00:52:59,750 --> 00:53:02,139
He was working against you,
and now I know why.

697
00:53:02,550 --> 00:53:05,826
He wants you to tell the whole world
you hated him.

698
00:53:06,830 --> 00:53:09,139
Maybe they think you hated him
enough to kill him.

699
00:53:09,870 --> 00:53:11,826
If you do that, you go to jail...

700
00:53:12,070 --> 00:53:13,344
...and he know that.

701
00:53:14,950 --> 00:53:16,781
Most important thing:

702
00:53:17,870 --> 00:53:21,829
You got to beg that boy's forgiveness
each and every day.

703
00:53:27,590 --> 00:53:29,421
Time for evil.

704
00:53:34,150 --> 00:53:36,584
Quick, quick.
Tell me his name.

705
00:53:37,070 --> 00:53:38,469
Finley Largent.

706
00:53:39,110 --> 00:53:43,661
When you get home, write his name
7 times on a piece of paper.

707
00:53:43,910 --> 00:53:45,901
Connect all the names into one.

708
00:53:46,150 --> 00:53:48,186
Dot no I's, cross no T's.

709
00:53:48,470 --> 00:53:50,745
Fold it twice and put it in your pocket.

710
00:53:55,110 --> 00:53:56,225
Get a picture.

711
00:53:56,470 --> 00:53:59,189
Sew up the mouth with dove's blood.

712
00:53:59,430 --> 00:54:00,579
Blacken the eyes.

713
00:54:00,830 --> 00:54:02,866
Now go!
I got works to do.

714
00:54:06,830 --> 00:54:07,865
Boy!

715
00:54:08,750 --> 00:54:10,468
Take these words to heart.

716
00:54:12,470 --> 00:54:14,620
To understand the living...

717
00:54:14,950 --> 00:54:17,418
...you got to commune with the dead.

718
00:54:20,750 --> 00:54:21,660
Now go!

719
00:54:21,910 --> 00:54:23,707
And don't you dare look back!

720
00:54:53,750 --> 00:54:55,103
On the grave...

721
00:54:55,470 --> 00:54:57,108
Who is Dr. Buzzard?

722
00:54:57,390 --> 00:54:59,346
Minerva was married to Dr. Buzzard...

723
00:54:59,590 --> 00:55:02,980
...the foremost voodoo practitioner
in Beaufort County.

724
00:55:03,230 --> 00:55:06,028
You may not know it,
but you are deep in voodoo country.

725
00:55:06,790 --> 00:55:09,099
I don't believe
in the hocus-pocus of it...

726
00:55:09,350 --> 00:55:11,739
...but the spiritual force behind it.

727
00:55:12,350 --> 00:55:15,148
The shiny dimes were easy...

728
00:55:15,390 --> 00:55:18,063
...but the virgin water
was a trick or two.

729
00:55:18,710 --> 00:55:21,588
How do you know she wouldn't know
the difference if it was tap water?

730
00:55:22,710 --> 00:55:24,541
Not by looking or taste...

731
00:55:24,790 --> 00:55:27,588
...but she would've known
in an instant by looking at my face.

732
00:55:32,710 --> 00:55:33,904
I think...

733
00:55:34,150 --> 00:55:36,948
...the photo-doctoring
is going to be good therapy.

734
00:55:39,070 --> 00:55:41,538
What about the pleas
for daily forgiveness?

735
00:55:42,790 --> 00:55:46,669
No, I don't think that's
going to be happening. Definitely not.

736
00:55:54,470 --> 00:55:55,983
- Thank you.
- Have a good day.

737
00:55:57,310 --> 00:55:58,709
- Hey, you.
- How are you?

738
00:55:58,950 --> 00:56:00,099
- How you doing?
- Good.

739
00:56:00,350 --> 00:56:01,305
You work here?

740
00:56:01,790 --> 00:56:03,462
What you see is what you get.

741
00:56:03,710 --> 00:56:04,938
Nothing wrong with that.

742
00:56:05,190 --> 00:56:06,703
Gee, thanks.

743
00:56:25,470 --> 00:56:26,698
These are nice.

744
00:56:27,150 --> 00:56:29,141
You want to send some flowers?

745
00:56:30,270 --> 00:56:32,420
I think so.
I don't know, though.

746
00:56:32,670 --> 00:56:34,149
It's kind of complicated.

747
00:56:34,750 --> 00:56:36,024
For whom?

748
00:56:36,950 --> 00:56:38,144
What's she like?

749
00:56:38,390 --> 00:56:40,142
I don't know her that well.

750
00:56:40,390 --> 00:56:41,584
Roses are a favorite.

751
00:56:41,830 --> 00:56:43,741
A bit presumptuous.

752
00:56:43,990 --> 00:56:45,309
How about...

753
00:56:45,550 --> 00:56:46,426
...poinsettias?

