1504
01:43:29,267 --> 01:43:31,178
Maybe you shouldn't testify.

1505
01:43:32,227 --> 01:43:34,900
John, how sweet. You really care.

1506
01:43:35,747 --> 01:43:38,466
Good. Because, guess what?
I'm testifying.

1507
01:43:38,707 --> 01:43:40,220
I am testifying.

1508
01:43:40,467 --> 01:43:43,425
You see, those folks think
they're using the Doll...

1509
01:43:43,667 --> 01:43:45,578
...but the Doll's using them right back.

1510
01:43:45,827 --> 01:43:50,537
I'm going to use that courtroom
as my coming-out party.

1511
01:43:50,787 --> 01:43:52,220
You see, you know who I am.

1512
01:43:52,467 --> 01:43:54,697
I'm the Lady chablis.

1513
01:43:54,947 --> 01:43:56,266
Hear me roar.

1514
01:43:56,507 --> 01:43:57,417
Look out!

1515
01:43:59,027 --> 01:44:01,302
Besides,
I've already bought a new ensemble.

1516
01:44:01,547 --> 01:44:03,981
- Really? Is it nice?
- You'll see, hon.

1517
01:44:04,467 --> 01:44:05,741
Listen to me.

1518
01:44:06,067 --> 01:44:07,659
We must get out of here.

1519
01:44:07,907 --> 01:44:10,865
It's rude of you to bust in on me.
I'd never do that to you.

1520
01:44:11,187 --> 01:44:13,382
Lav ella's mother
is about to have a seizure.

1521
01:44:13,627 --> 01:44:16,346
Somebody put a spoon in her mouth, then,
because I'm not leaving.

1522
01:44:16,587 --> 01:44:17,736
You're leaving now.

1523
01:44:17,987 --> 01:44:19,659
- I am not.
- I'll buy you a drink.

1524
01:44:19,907 --> 01:44:21,056
- Buy me a drink.
- Outside of here.

1525
01:44:21,307 --> 01:44:22,979
- Buy me a diamond.
- I'll buy you a diamond.

1526
01:44:23,227 --> 01:44:25,138
- Give me some.
- I'm not giving you shit.

1527
01:44:25,387 --> 01:44:26,900
Oh, come on!

1528
01:44:27,147 --> 01:44:28,580
You know I'm straight.

1529
01:44:28,827 --> 01:44:29,896
So am I.

1530
01:44:30,147 --> 01:44:32,138
Straight to my house. Let's go.

1531
01:44:38,467 --> 01:44:39,582
Raise your right hand.

1532
01:44:39,827 --> 01:44:44,218
Do you swear the evidence you're about
to give is the truth, so help you God?

1533
01:44:44,467 --> 01:44:45,343
I do.

1534
01:44:47,467 --> 01:44:49,025
Now, Miss De Veau...

1535
01:44:49,547 --> 01:44:53,176
...I'll ask you a question and
I want you to answer to the jury...

1536
01:44:53,427 --> 01:44:56,499
...so that they can understand.

1537
01:44:58,227 --> 01:45:01,139
Yes, and what is that?
You'd like me to explain my "T"?

1538
01:45:01,707 --> 01:45:03,425
Your "T"?

1539
01:45:05,387 --> 01:45:06,706
My "T."

1540
01:45:06,947 --> 01:45:08,778
Yeah, explain your "T"...

1541
01:45:09,027 --> 01:45:13,066
...in as plain a language
as you possibly can for our friends.

1542
01:45:13,307 --> 01:45:16,424
I will try my best to explain
to you jurors.

1543
01:45:16,667 --> 01:45:19,784
I could throw words and labels
at all of you...

1544
01:45:20,027 --> 01:45:21,699
...but you seem like nice people.

1545
01:45:22,227 --> 01:45:24,457
So I'm going to be open and honest.

1546
01:45:25,747 --> 01:45:28,545
I have a man's toolbox...

1547
01:45:29,307 --> 01:45:31,423
...but everything else about me
is pure lady.

1548
01:45:32,947 --> 01:45:34,426
I love to dress in women's clothes.

1549
01:45:35,387 --> 01:45:37,343
I love to go shopping.

1550
01:45:37,587 --> 01:45:39,498
I love to have my nails done...

1551
01:45:39,747 --> 01:45:42,181
...and I love men.

1552
01:45:45,507 --> 01:45:47,179
Any questions?

1553
01:45:49,587 --> 01:45:52,101
And, ma'am,
I hope you don't mind my saying...

1554
01:45:52,387 --> 01:45:55,379
...blue is definitely not your color.

1555
01:45:55,667 --> 01:45:57,419
Okay, gals, you're both pretty, now.

1556
01:45:58,067 --> 01:46:01,457
What I want to know
and want you to tell the jury is...

1557
01:46:01,707 --> 01:46:04,221
...how you and Billy Hanson first met.

1558
01:46:05,067 --> 01:46:08,218
Billy hit on me one night at the...
Strike that, Your Honor.

1559
01:46:08,747 --> 01:46:09,975
Billy and I clienteled.

1560
01:46:10,347 --> 01:46:11,336
"Clienteled."

1561
01:46:11,587 --> 01:46:13,384
Will you explain what that means?

1562
01:46:13,627 --> 01:46:18,143
We socialized together for a little
while, until he met my roommate Corinne.

1563
01:46:18,387 --> 01:46:20,617
Corinne.
Now, you telling me that...

1564
01:46:20,867 --> 01:46:24,382
...Corinne and Billy Hanson
were intimate?

1565
01:46:25,787 --> 01:46:27,857
Hot and intimate.

1566
01:46:30,147 --> 01:46:31,978
Will you tell the jury...

1567
01:46:32,427 --> 01:46:34,179
...did Billy Hanson use drugs?

1568
01:46:37,907 --> 01:46:41,616
Yes. Billy did pills, smoked pot...

1569
01:46:41,867 --> 01:46:43,141
...little coke.

1570
01:46:43,387 --> 01:46:45,617
He sold drugs.

1571
01:46:46,067 --> 01:46:50,583
He'd stay with us sometimes, so
sometimes we had stash around the house.

1572
01:46:52,867 --> 01:46:54,937
- Mrs. Chablis...
- Miss.

1573
01:46:55,347 --> 01:46:57,338
Course, Miss Chablis.

1574
01:46:58,587 --> 01:47:00,339
Do you yourself take drugs?

1575
01:47:02,147 --> 01:47:04,138
I smoke a little pot.

1576
01:47:04,387 --> 01:47:06,298
I'm a mellow kind of girl.

1577
01:47:07,067 --> 01:47:08,136
I understand.

1578
01:47:08,507 --> 01:47:12,500
Well, tell me
if you know what effect, if any...

1579
01:47:12,747 --> 01:47:15,136
...these drugs
had on the relationship...

1580
01:47:15,387 --> 01:47:17,742
...between your friend Corinne
and Billy.

1581
01:47:17,987 --> 01:47:22,219
Well, now, when Billy got high,
he could be very, very hostile.

1582
01:47:22,947 --> 01:47:24,346
Hostile, when he was high.

1583
01:47:24,587 --> 01:47:27,385
Would you explain to the jury
what you mean by hostile?

1584
01:47:27,627 --> 01:47:30,858
I can do more than that, hon.
Let me show you something.

1585
01:47:31,107 --> 01:47:33,143
Look at my driver's license.

1586
01:47:33,387 --> 01:47:35,662
- Just a minute.
- Objection.

1587
01:47:35,987 --> 01:47:36,942
This isn't proper.

1588
01:47:37,187 --> 01:47:38,256
Be quiet.

1589
01:47:38,507 --> 01:47:39,542
I'll handle this.

1590
01:47:39,787 --> 01:47:40,663
Just a minute.

1591
01:47:40,907 --> 01:47:42,579
That's not proper procedure.

1592
01:47:44,427 --> 01:47:45,985
Pick up this item, please.

1593
01:47:46,947 --> 01:47:50,906
My eye. He hit me. I looked like
that dog from <i>The Little Rascals.</i>

1594
01:47:51,147 --> 01:47:54,822
Members of the jury, I'm instructing you
to disregard this outburst.

1595
01:47:55,067 --> 01:47:57,137
Pay no attention to that picture.

1596
01:47:58,427 --> 01:48:00,702
Your Honor? It's the truth.
I'm not lying.

1597
01:48:00,947 --> 01:48:02,858
Your Honor, the people...

1598
01:48:03,187 --> 01:48:04,222
Be quiet.

1599
01:48:04,467 --> 01:48:07,220
Now we got to get this thing
under control.

1600
01:48:07,467 --> 01:48:09,025
You sit down, Mr. De Veau.

1601
01:48:09,267 --> 01:48:11,417
Miss De v eau. I'm a single girl.

1602
01:48:11,787 --> 01:48:13,459
Miss De Veau, whatever.

1603
01:48:13,707 --> 01:48:14,662
Have a seat.

1604
01:48:15,427 --> 01:48:18,021
Okay, but please don't get too huffy.

1605
01:48:18,427 --> 01:48:20,019
You listen to me.

1606
01:48:21,227 --> 01:48:23,661
I'm in charge of this courtroom,
not you.

1607
01:48:23,907 --> 01:48:25,226
Here's the way it works:

1608
01:48:25,467 --> 01:48:28,345
These lawyers
are going to ask you questions...

1609
01:48:28,587 --> 01:48:29,986
...and you answer them.

1610
01:48:30,427 --> 01:48:32,338
If I tell you to stop, you stop.

1611
01:48:33,267 --> 01:48:35,258
If I tell you to sit, you sit.

1612
01:48:35,507 --> 01:48:38,863
And I don't want you to communicate
directly with that jury.

1613
01:48:39,107 --> 01:48:40,506
Don't produce any more items.

1614
01:48:41,027 --> 01:48:44,144
Don't show any photographs.
Do you understand that?

1615
01:48:45,707 --> 01:48:47,902
Yes, Your Honor.
I understand.

1616
01:48:52,427 --> 01:48:54,861
Mrs. Wright threw in some gumbo.

1617
01:48:55,987 --> 01:48:57,306
I got you cigarettes.

1618
01:48:58,667 --> 01:49:02,785
Thank you. How are we coming
with our character witnesses?

1619
01:49:03,027 --> 01:49:07,703
I thought we would limit it to 3 because
we don't need too much fawning and...

1620
01:49:08,347 --> 01:49:09,541
Why not?

1621
01:49:09,787 --> 01:49:12,221
Tell him how many friends
are lining up to defend me.

1622
01:49:12,467 --> 01:49:15,539
I suggest Wanda Javitz.
She has a commanding vocal presence.

1623
01:49:15,787 --> 01:49:17,937
She declined, Jim...

1624
01:49:18,187 --> 01:49:19,461
...along with some others.

1625
01:49:20,827 --> 01:49:21,976
Declined?

1626
01:49:27,267 --> 01:49:29,178
They clamored for my friendship.

1627
01:49:29,427 --> 01:49:32,624
Hoping and praying
for invitations to my parties.

1628
01:49:33,587 --> 01:49:35,498
Where were their judgments then?

1629
01:49:37,147 --> 01:49:40,742
I hope Wanda knows this puts her
in the out box for my Christmas party.

1630
01:49:42,067 --> 01:49:45,139
I don't think we have to worry
about character witnesses.

1631
01:49:45,387 --> 01:49:46,661
They got theirs, we got ours.

1632
01:49:47,627 --> 01:49:49,060
When do I take the stand?

1633
01:49:49,747 --> 01:49:50,702
Last.

1634
01:49:51,107 --> 01:49:52,096
Good.

1635
01:49:52,347 --> 01:49:55,737
They'll have heard all the theories.
We'll finish with the truth.

1636
01:49:55,987 --> 01:49:57,136
I look forward to this.

1637
01:49:57,387 --> 01:50:01,824
It's important, not that I'm acquitted,
but that everyone knows I'm innocent.

1638
01:50:03,547 --> 01:50:06,220
I refuse to live in a world
where whispers become fact.

1639
01:50:06,467 --> 01:50:09,345
Guilty men murmur.
The innocent shout to the rafters.

1640
01:50:09,587 --> 01:50:10,861
Hear, hear.

1641
01:50:11,907 --> 01:50:16,378
We may need you to come clean
about the relationship with Billy.

1642
01:50:18,267 --> 01:50:19,700
Your sexuality, Jim.

1643
01:50:20,467 --> 01:50:23,777
Finley's taken this thing in a direction
we didn't count on.

1644
01:50:24,027 --> 01:50:26,222
His own private witch-hunt.

1645
01:50:28,227 --> 01:50:30,104
It's going to destroy Mother.

1646
01:50:31,907 --> 01:50:33,386
Jim, she was in court.

1647
01:50:33,627 --> 01:50:34,980
She heard George Tucker.

1648
01:50:35,467 --> 01:50:37,503
Face it, she already knows.

1649
01:50:38,347 --> 01:50:40,178
Not from me she doesn't.

1650
01:50:47,027 --> 01:50:48,938
What if she wasn't in court?

1651
01:50:59,627 --> 01:51:01,618
What's the matter?
Gunpowder?

1652
01:51:04,387 --> 01:51:06,423
Damn gunshot residue test.

1653
01:51:06,667 --> 01:51:10,057
Your expert witness covered it.
He said the tests are unreliable.

1654
01:51:10,307 --> 01:51:12,104
Jury thinks that's a cop-out.

1655
01:51:12,587 --> 01:51:14,862
Every one of them knows Doc Poe.

1656
01:51:15,787 --> 01:51:18,859
Why listen to some egghead
from up north? No offense.

1657
01:51:19,107 --> 01:51:20,222
No, none taken.

1658
01:51:21,067 --> 01:51:24,662
He said gunpowder wipes off.
Maybe when they handled the body...

1659
01:51:24,907 --> 01:51:26,863
Boone says he bagged them.

1660
01:51:27,627 --> 01:51:31,302
Doc Poe says they were bagged
when he performed the autopsy.

1661
01:51:31,947 --> 01:51:34,142
When are they going to get wiped off?

1662
01:51:35,547 --> 01:51:36,741
I don't know.

1663
01:51:40,747 --> 01:51:44,501
Do you remember when you told me
that dead men tell no tales?

1664
01:51:46,187 --> 01:51:47,302
See, I think...

1665
01:51:47,547 --> 01:51:51,301
...that may be true,
but it does not apply here.

1666
01:51:51,907 --> 01:51:53,545
I mean, look around.

1667
01:51:54,867 --> 01:51:58,064
Every picture on every wall in this town
is of someone who's gone.

1668
01:51:58,307 --> 01:52:01,458
Every story you hear begins
with someone who's dead.

1669
01:52:02,347 --> 01:52:06,659
The only living national treasure
you have is your own slavering mutt.

1670
01:52:07,387 --> 01:52:11,460
You writing your book?
What the hell are you talking about?

1671
01:52:11,707 --> 01:52:14,460
Billy Hanson may not be talking,
but his hands are.

1672
01:52:14,947 --> 01:52:16,824
Billy Hanson's hands?

1673
01:52:19,947 --> 01:52:21,221
I got to go.

1674
01:52:23,507 --> 01:52:24,781
Where you going?

1675
01:52:28,067 --> 01:52:29,898
"To understand the living...

1676
01:52:30,347 --> 01:52:32,781
...you got to commune with the dead.

1677
01:52:33,387 --> 01:52:34,661
I need Shango.

1678
01:52:37,387 --> 01:52:38,536
Now go.

1679
01:52:38,787 --> 01:52:40,937
And don't you dare look back."

1680
01:52:42,427 --> 01:52:45,305
I hope you can communicate
with someone.

1681
01:52:51,147 --> 01:52:53,138
Feel like going for a walk?

1682
01:52:54,947 --> 01:52:56,300
Where you headed?

1683
01:52:57,307 --> 01:53:00,538
I don't know, I was thinking about
maybe stopping by the morgue.

1684
01:53:01,347 --> 01:53:03,065
Are you a necrophiliac or something?

1685
01:53:03,307 --> 01:53:05,423
We agreed you wouldn't talk
about my ex-wife.

1686
01:53:05,707 --> 01:53:08,540
- How long you been at the bar?
- Long enough. It'll be fun.

1687
01:53:08,787 --> 01:53:10,186
Why do you want to go?

1688
01:53:10,427 --> 01:53:13,260
If I could answer that question,
I wouldn't have to go.

1689
01:53:13,507 --> 01:53:17,341
The morgue's closed, and by tomorrow
this won't seem like such a good idea.

1690
01:53:17,587 --> 01:53:22,297
Precisely. I'll break in if I have to.
I don't care. I'll pretend I'm dead.

1691
01:53:23,067 --> 01:53:25,581
- You sure you want to do this?
- I think so.

1692
01:53:26,507 --> 01:53:28,816
There is a back way...

1693
01:53:29,067 --> 01:53:31,786
...a hallway off the emergency room.
It's off-limits.

1694
01:53:32,027 --> 01:53:34,302
- How do you know that?
- I candy-striped one summer.

1695
01:53:34,547 --> 01:53:35,946
At the morgue?

1696
01:53:36,307 --> 01:53:38,502
- We'll create a distraction...
- We?

1697
01:53:38,747 --> 01:53:42,706
You create the distraction
and I'll just slip in and check it out.

1698
01:53:44,347 --> 01:53:46,019
No, you'll get lost.

1699
01:53:46,627 --> 01:53:49,187
All right, it's a 3-man job.
Where's Joe?

1700
01:53:49,427 --> 01:53:52,544
Perfect casting, but he's out of town
till tomorrow.

1701
01:53:54,187 --> 01:53:56,337
Who do we know
who can cause a commotion?

1702
01:54:03,947 --> 01:54:05,221
Hello! Nurse!

1703
01:54:09,307 --> 01:54:10,786
- What's wrong with her?
- Her stomach.

1704
01:54:11,027 --> 01:54:12,619
Appendicitis.
My water broke.

1705
01:54:12,867 --> 01:54:15,825
Get the doctor to exam 4.
Water broke? She's pregnant.

1706
01:54:16,067 --> 01:54:18,058
I don't know what's up. Just help.

1707
01:54:18,307 --> 01:54:20,423
- What's wrong?
- A stomach problem.

1708
01:54:20,667 --> 01:54:22,339
Let's get her up on the table.

1709
01:54:29,147 --> 01:54:30,421
Okay, here we are.

1710
01:54:30,667 --> 01:54:32,225
Commune away.

1711
01:54:32,467 --> 01:54:33,661
Is this where it hurts?

1712
01:54:33,907 --> 01:54:35,386
Just...
Oh, doctor, wait.

1713
01:54:36,187 --> 01:54:37,063
Here?

1714
01:54:37,307 --> 01:54:40,026
You know, I think you need to go
just a little bit lower.

1715
01:54:40,867 --> 01:54:41,936
Never been in a morgue.

1716
01:54:42,187 --> 01:54:43,620
What are we looking for?

1717
01:54:45,627 --> 01:54:48,983
I don't know. Something about
the bagging of the hands.

1718
01:54:49,467 --> 01:54:51,537
Oh, look. Teddy Lipscomb.

1719
01:54:52,347 --> 01:54:53,462
Excuse me?

1720
01:54:53,987 --> 01:54:57,104
- You know this guy?
- Yeah, he was my dad's dentist.

1721
01:54:57,827 --> 01:54:59,465
Oh, man!

1722
01:55:01,107 --> 01:55:01,983
Cardiac arrest.

1723
01:55:02,227 --> 01:55:06,618
Right. Medical term for dying in the
arms of a 25-year-old cocktail waitress.

1724
01:55:06,867 --> 01:55:07,617
Poor guy.

1725
01:55:09,707 --> 01:55:12,938
See, now, remind me
never to get sick in Savannah.

1726
01:55:13,187 --> 01:55:15,098
He's wearing a hospital I.D. Bracelet.

1727
01:55:15,347 --> 01:55:18,145
You're supposed to get well
in hospitals, but not in this city.

1728
01:55:18,467 --> 01:55:22,745
The morgue doesn't have its own ramp,
so all DOA's come through emergency.

1729
01:55:22,987 --> 01:55:25,217
Technically, they'd have to be admitted.

1730
01:55:27,827 --> 01:55:29,146
They're all wearing bracelets.

1731
01:55:29,387 --> 01:55:32,345
It's bureaucratic red tape.
I told you, I candy-striped.

1732
01:55:32,587 --> 01:55:34,498
You did.
That's like volunteer work?

1733
01:55:34,747 --> 01:55:37,022
Yeah, cute little striped outfit,
short skirt.

1734
01:55:37,267 --> 01:55:38,336
Girl Scouts.

1735
01:55:39,067 --> 01:55:40,739
- Is this where it hurts?
- Almost.

1736
01:55:40,987 --> 01:55:43,103
Just a tad bit...

1737
01:55:43,347 --> 01:55:45,907
That's the spot.
I love you.

1738
01:55:46,187 --> 01:55:49,384
I love you.
Oh, Dr. Feelgood, that's the spot.

1739
01:55:49,627 --> 01:55:50,821
You got it.

1740
01:55:56,147 --> 01:56:00,186
You wouldn't take a bag off
to put an I.D. Bracelet on, would you?

1741
01:56:01,027 --> 01:56:02,346
Yeah, probably.

1742
01:56:02,587 --> 01:56:03,542
Maybe.

1743
01:56:07,987 --> 01:56:10,740
Pleasure's been all mine, Doctor.

1744
01:56:11,227 --> 01:56:12,262
How you doing, Mom?

1745
01:56:12,507 --> 01:56:14,782
Nurse, I have a question for you.

1746
01:56:15,027 --> 01:56:17,780
Were you on duty the night
Billy Hanson's body came in?

1747
01:56:18,027 --> 01:56:19,699
I was.
How'd you get back there?

1748
01:56:19,947 --> 01:56:22,507
Back door.
I was here with the sick lady?

1749
01:56:22,747 --> 01:56:25,659
I have a question.
Hanson's hands were bagged.

1750
01:56:25,907 --> 01:56:27,545
Someone had to put the I.D. Bracelet on.

1751
01:56:27,787 --> 01:56:30,585
Would you take the bag off
to slide the bracelet on?

1752
01:56:30,827 --> 01:56:32,658
No, they snap on.

1753
01:56:33,627 --> 01:56:34,946
They snap on?

1754
01:56:36,747 --> 01:56:37,657
Thank you.

1755
01:56:37,907 --> 01:56:40,660
It was easier with him
because I bagged him after.

1756
01:56:43,707 --> 01:56:44,822
Excuse me?

1757
01:56:45,387 --> 01:56:49,858
Doc Poe called from the crime scene and
said to bag the hands when he came in.

1758
01:56:51,907 --> 01:56:53,260
You bagged the hands?

1759
01:56:53,707 --> 01:56:56,221
Yes, I wrote it up
on the admission sheet.

1760
01:56:56,467 --> 01:56:57,616
May I see that?

1761
01:57:00,427 --> 01:57:02,577
We'll let Sonny tell you.
He'll be here any minute.

1762
01:57:02,827 --> 01:57:06,342
Before Sonny gets here,
I'd like to run something by you.

1763
01:57:06,587 --> 01:57:08,737
- Fire away.
- About that night.

1764
01:57:16,227 --> 01:57:17,580
What do you got?

1765
01:57:19,347 --> 01:57:21,907
The evening started out
as I've always said.

1766
01:57:23,027 --> 01:57:24,096
<i>The argument...</i>

1767
01:57:24,507 --> 01:57:25,622
<i>... the shouting...</i>

1768
01:57:29,227 --> 01:57:31,218
You let me down, like everyone else.

1769
01:57:32,067 --> 01:57:35,662
My mama let me down. She hates me
because I look like my daddy.

1770
01:57:35,907 --> 01:57:38,341
- What are you yelling about?
- I'm yelling about you!

1771
01:57:38,587 --> 01:57:42,705
It's fine for you to talk to me
about living in this grandeur and all.

1772
01:57:42,947 --> 01:57:44,938
You could do it
if you took responsibility.

1773
01:57:45,187 --> 01:57:46,700
Bullshit, Jim!

1774
01:57:46,947 --> 01:57:49,984
If you don't like it,
why don't you just get the hell out?!

1775
01:57:50,267 --> 01:57:51,620
Get the hell out.

1776
01:57:51,867 --> 01:57:54,586
This candle is about ready
to go through that painting!

1777
01:57:54,827 --> 01:57:58,615
I'll stop paying the insurance
on your Camaro.

1778
01:57:58,867 --> 01:58:02,542
You want to leave,
you can do it tomorrow morning.

1779
01:58:05,387 --> 01:58:06,820
<i>The damaged clock...</i>

1780
01:58:17,867 --> 01:58:19,016
Goddamn it.

1781
01:58:19,267 --> 01:58:22,418
Walk into my house
and ruin my furniture. I've had it.

1782
01:58:22,667 --> 01:58:25,261
You're going to jail, young man.
That's it.

1783
01:58:26,667 --> 01:58:28,419
<i>Billy pointing the Luger...</i>

1784
01:58:28,667 --> 01:58:30,146
I may be leaving tomorrow...

1785
01:58:31,027 --> 01:58:32,142
...but goddamn it...

1786
01:58:32,507 --> 01:58:35,305
<i>But here's the difference:</i>
<i>When he pulled the trigger...</i>

1787
01:58:35,547 --> 01:58:36,423
...you're leaving tonight.

1788
01:58:37,387 --> 01:58:38,422
<i>... nothing happened.</i>

1789
01:58:38,667 --> 01:58:40,783
<i>The gun was on safety.</i>

1790
01:58:41,027 --> 01:58:44,178
<i>As he fumbled to take the safety off,</i>
<i>I grabbed my own gun...</i>

1791
01:58:49,987 --> 01:58:51,215
<i>... and I shot him.</i>

1792
01:59:07,147 --> 01:59:08,421
He fell dead.

1793
01:59:13,707 --> 01:59:15,538
He never fired?

1794
01:59:17,187 --> 01:59:18,142
No.

1795
01:59:19,307 --> 01:59:21,775
<i>I thought, "What have you done?!"</i>

1796
01:59:51,627 --> 01:59:53,265
It explains...

1797
01:59:53,507 --> 01:59:56,544
...why there's no powder
on Billy's hands.

1798
01:59:56,787 --> 02:00:00,223
When I sit on that stand
and I tell this to the jury...

1799
02:00:00,467 --> 02:00:01,946
...Largent's case...

1800
02:00:02,187 --> 02:00:03,905
...will crumble.

1801
02:00:11,027 --> 02:00:12,904
I don't see how you figure that.

1802
02:00:14,827 --> 02:00:16,579
If you tell that story...

1803
02:00:17,107 --> 02:00:18,426
...you're admitting...

1804
02:00:18,667 --> 02:00:19,895
...that you lied.

1805
02:00:22,227 --> 02:00:23,376
Lied to everyone.

1806
02:00:23,627 --> 02:00:24,946
The police...

1807
02:00:25,307 --> 02:00:26,660
...the press...

1808
02:00:28,347 --> 02:00:29,621
...everyone.

1809
02:00:32,587 --> 02:00:33,656
Yes.

1810
02:00:35,307 --> 02:00:36,660
Of course.

1811
02:00:38,827 --> 02:00:43,218
I'd rather be convicted of lying
than of murder.

1812
02:00:45,227 --> 02:00:46,182
So...

1813
02:00:47,187 --> 02:00:48,256
Hey, coach.

1814
02:00:48,507 --> 02:00:49,656
We got it.

1815
02:00:51,107 --> 02:00:52,096
Keep your seat.

1816
02:00:52,827 --> 02:00:54,818
Sonny, I need to tell you something.

1817
02:00:55,307 --> 02:00:58,583
Now, me first.
You know that gunshot residue test?

1818
02:00:58,827 --> 02:01:01,580
What I have to say has direct bearing
on the gunshot residue...

1819
02:01:01,827 --> 02:01:03,101
Can I get this out?

1820
02:01:06,747 --> 02:01:08,465
We got them by the gonads.

1821
02:01:08,707 --> 02:01:10,584
Detective Boone lied.

1822
02:01:11,627 --> 02:01:15,984
Doc Poe called the admitting nurse
and told her to bag the hands...

1823
02:01:16,227 --> 02:01:17,979
...if they were not already.

1824
02:01:18,227 --> 02:01:19,785
Which she did.

1825
02:01:20,067 --> 02:01:21,466
Right here in this document.

1826
02:01:27,147 --> 02:01:31,504
Many could have handled the body
between the crime scene and the hospital.

1827
02:01:32,227 --> 02:01:34,536
Which explains how the powder
got rubbed off.

1828
02:01:35,267 --> 02:01:36,416
There it is.

1829
02:01:37,307 --> 02:01:41,983
The death knell to Finley Largent's
precious gunshot residue test.

1830
02:01:45,467 --> 02:01:46,502
Your turn.

1831
02:01:47,387 --> 02:01:48,422
What was it?

1832
02:01:52,667 --> 02:01:54,259
Oh, it's not important.

1833
02:02:01,067 --> 02:02:02,341
Take a look here.

1834
02:02:03,387 --> 02:02:05,298
We got them, Jimbo.

1835
02:02:13,747 --> 02:02:15,339
Going somewhere, coach?

1836
02:02:23,667 --> 02:02:25,146
What's his story?

1837
02:02:45,427 --> 02:02:47,224
You're still under oath.

1838
02:02:47,947 --> 02:02:48,857
Frank...

1839
02:02:50,027 --> 02:02:52,302
...are you absolutely sure...

1840
02:02:52,547 --> 02:02:55,857
...that you bagged Billy Hanson's hands
at Mercer House?

1841
02:02:56,107 --> 02:02:57,222
Yes.

1842
02:03:00,787 --> 02:03:02,857
I have no further questions.

1843
02:03:03,427 --> 02:03:05,338
Redirect, Mr. Largent?

1844
02:03:09,667 --> 02:03:10,702
No, Your Honor.

1845
02:03:11,507 --> 02:03:16,058
Detective, you're excused. You're still
under subpoena. Thank you very much.

1846
02:03:16,547 --> 02:03:19,107
Defense calls Sara Warren...

1847
02:03:19,347 --> 02:03:20,462
...R.N.

1848
02:03:25,547 --> 02:03:27,299
You won't find her in your notes.

1849
02:03:27,547 --> 02:03:29,378
She's not on your list, Finley.

1850
02:03:29,627 --> 02:03:33,745
Sara Warren is a direct rebuttal
to the testimony of Detective Boone.

1851
02:03:34,667 --> 02:03:36,862
She is, in fact, an admitting nurse...

1852
02:03:37,107 --> 02:03:38,699
...at Chandler Emergency Room.

1853
02:03:59,267 --> 02:04:03,738
<i>Mr. Williams, will you describe</i>
<i>your relationship with the deceased?</i>

1854
02:04:05,987 --> 02:04:10,139
I met Billy Hanson when he came around
to the house wanting a job.

1855
02:04:11,067 --> 02:04:11,977
So...

1856
02:04:12,227 --> 02:04:14,695
...I hired him in the workshop
to refinish furniture.

1857
02:04:14,947 --> 02:04:17,461
He had some talent,
and I wanted to encourage him.

1858
02:04:17,987 --> 02:04:19,261
During this time...

1859
02:04:19,507 --> 02:04:23,295
...I developed hypoglycemia. I
blacked-out at times. I don't eat well.

1860
02:04:23,547 --> 02:04:25,219
The doctor told me...

1861
02:04:25,467 --> 02:04:28,857
...it was not good for me to be alone
when this condition occurs.

1862
02:04:29,107 --> 02:04:30,904
So Billy would stay over...

1863
02:04:31,147 --> 02:04:32,899
...and take care of me
when I wasn't well.

1864
02:04:33,147 --> 02:04:36,344
He did not live at Mercer House,
as has been stated.

1865
02:04:39,387 --> 02:04:44,177
Is that the full extent of your
relationship with Billy Hanson?

1866
02:04:46,147 --> 02:04:50,425
No. Over time, it evolved
into something less formal.

1867
02:04:51,347 --> 02:04:52,496
We became intimate.

1868
02:04:53,187 --> 02:04:55,018
Billy could be very charming.

1869
02:04:55,267 --> 02:04:57,622
He had his girlfriends and I had mine.

1870
02:04:58,107 --> 02:04:59,096
But to me...

1871
02:04:59,347 --> 02:05:01,702
...sex is a perfectly natural thing.

1872
02:05:02,027 --> 02:05:03,983
It didn't bother me.
It didn't bother him.

1873
02:05:04,547 --> 02:05:09,063
It was just an occasional natural
occurrence between consenting adults.

1874
02:05:14,747 --> 02:05:16,658
Would you describe to the jury...

1875
02:05:16,907 --> 02:05:19,660
...the events
that occurred in your house...

1876
02:05:19,907 --> 02:05:21,181
...after the party?

1877
02:05:23,387 --> 02:05:26,265
By the time Billy got back to the house
he was quite high...

1878
02:05:26,507 --> 02:05:29,340
...and we got into an argument
about a planned trip to London.

1879
02:05:29,747 --> 02:05:33,501
I was going to an auction, and Billy was
to accompany me because of my condition.

1880
02:05:34,987 --> 02:05:37,342
But he insisted on taking
marijuana cigarettes.

1881
02:05:37,587 --> 02:05:41,057
I do not approve of drugs
and I told him he could not go.

1882
02:05:41,307 --> 02:05:44,185
He became verbally abusive
and I ordered Billy out of the house.

1883
02:05:44,427 --> 02:05:45,780
He went into the hallway.

1884
02:05:46,027 --> 02:05:49,861
The argument continued there.
Then he knocked over a clock.

1885
02:05:51,027 --> 02:05:54,383
I went to call the police.
He followed me with a gun.

1886
02:05:54,627 --> 02:05:55,742
<i>He said...</i>

1887
02:05:57,267 --> 02:05:59,178
...and I'll never forget this:

1888
02:05:59,427 --> 02:06:00,826
<i>"I might leave tomorrow...</i>

1889
02:06:01,067 --> 02:06:03,535
...but goddamn it,
you're leaving tonight."

1890
02:06:05,987 --> 02:06:07,056
I saw that Luger...

1891
02:06:07,307 --> 02:06:08,103
<i>... and moved.</i>

1892
02:06:08,347 --> 02:06:10,463
I reached in a drawer
for my own weapon.

1893
02:06:10,707 --> 02:06:12,459
As I came up,
the first shot...

1894
02:06:13,027 --> 02:06:14,585
<i>... I felt breeze by my shoulder.</i>

1895
02:06:19,027 --> 02:06:20,016
And I fired.

1896
02:06:23,507 --> 02:06:25,020
I don't remember how many times.

1897
02:06:27,707 --> 02:06:29,186
<i>It was horrible.</i>

1898
02:06:53,787 --> 02:06:55,664
<i>We're all Savannahians.</i>

1899
02:06:55,907 --> 02:06:59,058
<i>Our paths cross from time to time.</i>

1900
02:06:59,547 --> 02:07:00,980
<i>We greet each other.</i>

1901
02:07:01,427 --> 02:07:03,497
<i>Smile here, nod there.</i>

1902
02:07:04,467 --> 02:07:06,423
<i>But even if we don 't know each other...</i>

1903
02:07:07,187 --> 02:07:08,939
<i>... we have one thing in common.</i>

1904
02:07:10,147 --> 02:07:12,980
<i>This beautiful place where we all live.</i>

1905
02:07:14,067 --> 02:07:15,739
<i>And as one Savannahian...</i>

1906
02:07:15,987 --> 02:07:17,136
<i>... to 12...</i>

1907
02:07:17,987 --> 02:07:21,423
<i>... I'd like to thank you</i>
<i>for your civic pride...</i>

1908
02:07:21,787 --> 02:07:23,220
<i>... for your diligence...</i>

1909
02:07:23,667 --> 02:07:25,464
<i>... and here in this courtroom...</i>

1910
02:07:25,947 --> 02:07:27,505
<i>... for your rapt attention.</i>

1911
02:07:27,747 --> 02:07:29,783
I've watched you taking notes.

1912
02:07:30,947 --> 02:07:33,905
The prosecution
started this whole thing...

1913
02:07:34,147 --> 02:07:36,615
...quoting someone
by the name of Hobbes.

1914
02:07:36,867 --> 02:07:38,300
I don't know who that is...

1915
02:07:39,547 --> 02:07:40,343
...but...

1916
02:07:40,627 --> 02:07:43,221
...I do know who Perry Mason is.

1917
02:07:43,907 --> 02:07:44,976
You watch <i>Perry Mason?</i>

1918
02:07:46,267 --> 02:07:47,256
I do.

1919
02:07:48,187 --> 02:07:49,540
And I got to thinking...

1920
02:07:49,787 --> 02:07:51,698
...if some TV writer...

1921
02:07:52,227 --> 02:07:54,218
...was to come to Perry Mason
and say...

1922
02:07:54,467 --> 02:07:58,301
..."Here you are, Mr. Raymond Burr,
here's a story like this."

1923
02:07:58,547 --> 02:08:00,219
You know what I think he'd say?

1924
02:08:00,467 --> 02:08:02,219
I think old Raymond would say...

1925
02:08:02,387 --> 02:08:04,855
"That's not a very good story.

1926
02:08:05,107 --> 02:08:07,621
I wouldn't have to be
a very good lawyer...

1927
02:08:07,867 --> 02:08:10,062
...to get that man off,
now would I?"

1928
02:08:10,907 --> 02:08:12,056
He'd be right!

1929
02:08:14,067 --> 02:08:15,056
Because...

1930
02:08:15,347 --> 02:08:19,181
...by all the evidence,
Jim Williams is an innocent man.

1931
02:08:20,947 --> 02:08:22,539
But I'm not Perry Mason.

1932
02:08:23,987 --> 02:08:25,943
I'm not some Tv lawyer.

1933
02:08:27,147 --> 02:08:31,857
So I got to scratch and tear
at the prosecution's case...

1934
02:08:32,627 --> 02:08:35,460
...trying to whittle it down to nothing.

1935
02:08:36,107 --> 02:08:38,257
And darned if I don't think I have!

1936
02:08:40,107 --> 02:08:44,737
Because the fabrication
of the prosecution's case is in pieces.

1937
02:08:45,027 --> 02:08:47,700
When you consider
how Detective Boone...

1938
02:08:47,947 --> 02:08:52,179
...has consistently lied
about bagging the hands.

1939
02:08:55,747 --> 02:08:57,305
Does that surprise you...

1940
02:08:58,307 --> 02:09:00,059
...that a detective would lie?

1941
02:09:01,507 --> 02:09:03,145
Of course he will.

1942
02:09:03,747 --> 02:09:05,260
He's not a bad man.

1943
02:09:05,507 --> 02:09:07,782
But how else will he play the cards...

1944
02:09:08,067 --> 02:09:10,706
...that have been dealt to him
from a pack of lies?

1945
02:09:13,227 --> 02:09:14,501
If Jim Williams...

1946
02:09:15,187 --> 02:09:16,905
...is guilty of anything...

1947
02:09:17,947 --> 02:09:20,142
...he's guilty of bad association.

1948
02:09:21,547 --> 02:09:23,936
But that's not why he's on trial for.

1949
02:09:24,947 --> 02:09:26,619
If you don't like...

1950
02:09:26,867 --> 02:09:30,337
...or if you don't cotton
to his lifestyle...

1951
02:09:30,867 --> 02:09:32,459
...just think about this:

1952
02:09:33,067 --> 02:09:35,058
We deal with these people all the time.

1953
02:09:35,387 --> 02:09:36,422
Some good...

1954
02:09:36,667 --> 02:09:37,941
...some bad.

1955
02:09:39,467 --> 02:09:41,105
They're a part of our community.

1956
02:09:42,867 --> 02:09:44,983
You can't judge a man for that.

1957
02:09:45,907 --> 02:09:47,306
This is God's world.

1958
02:09:48,267 --> 02:09:50,178
Let God be the judge of that.

1959
02:09:51,827 --> 02:09:53,306
And let you good folks...

1960
02:09:54,347 --> 02:09:55,939
...be the judge of this.

1961
02:09:58,547 --> 02:09:59,821
Come on, now.

1962
02:10:02,907 --> 02:10:04,625
You let this man go home.

1963
02:10:08,827 --> 02:10:10,055
He's had enough.

1964
02:10:16,587 --> 02:10:17,702
Thank you.

1965
02:10:54,427 --> 02:10:57,737
Mr. Foreman,
has the jury reached a verdict?

1966
02:10:58,507 --> 02:11:00,020
Yes, we have, Your Honor.

1967
02:11:00,747 --> 02:11:01,975
Is it unanimous?

1968
02:11:03,067 --> 02:11:04,136
Yes!

1969
02:11:08,547 --> 02:11:10,185
Hand it to the sheriff, please.

1970
02:11:22,827 --> 02:11:24,306
Pick that up.

1971
02:11:28,627 --> 02:11:29,980
Hand it to me.

1972
02:11:38,187 --> 02:11:39,745
Give it back to him.

1973
02:11:50,667 --> 02:11:53,227
Defendant and attorneys,
rise, please.

1974
02:11:56,667 --> 02:11:58,259
Publish the verdict.

1975
02:12:00,747 --> 02:12:03,386
"We, the jury,
find the defendant...

1976
02:12:04,747 --> 02:12:05,782
...not guilty."

1977
02:12:14,947 --> 02:12:17,780
Members of the jury,
this concludes your work.

1978
02:12:18,027 --> 02:12:21,986
You've rendered great service
to Savannah and Chatham County.

1979
02:12:22,267 --> 02:12:25,100
I'm going to dismiss you now
with the thanks of the court.

1980
02:12:38,747 --> 02:12:39,975
Congratulations, Jim.

1981
02:12:40,227 --> 02:12:41,376
Thank you, John.

1982
02:13:12,387 --> 02:13:13,706
Hey, boy!

1983
02:13:18,667 --> 02:13:20,066
What do you got?

1984
02:13:21,027 --> 02:13:22,426
Come on down.

1985
02:13:23,467 --> 02:13:25,537
We gots to go visit the boy.

1986
02:13:28,987 --> 02:13:31,547
We got to make him
quit working James.

1987
02:13:32,267 --> 02:13:34,144
Trial's over, Minerva.

1988
02:13:34,827 --> 02:13:37,022
Billy can't do anything to James now.

1989
02:13:38,067 --> 02:13:39,659
Why I come to you?

1990
02:13:40,467 --> 02:13:42,025
Because you...

1991
02:13:42,267 --> 02:13:44,781
...out of everybody,
know it ain't over yet.

1992
02:13:46,427 --> 02:13:51,455
I know, the boy know, and you know
justice ain't been done yet.

1993
02:13:57,507 --> 02:13:59,145
I'll come down for a minute.

1994
02:14:02,187 --> 02:14:03,700
I don't know about this.

1995
02:14:03,947 --> 02:14:06,780
That's exactly why you come this far.

1996
02:14:33,267 --> 02:14:36,100
Billy always loved Wild Turkey.

1997
02:14:36,947 --> 02:14:38,619
He ain't happy here.

1998
02:14:41,587 --> 02:14:43,418
Ain't what he thought it would be.

1999
02:14:46,107 --> 02:14:49,417
If you ain't in heaven yet, you want
to get there, don't you, boy?

2000
02:14:52,107 --> 02:14:55,179
The only way you're going to get up...

2001
02:14:55,427 --> 02:14:57,895
...is if you quit playing with James.

2002
02:15:10,467 --> 02:15:12,901
I has influence with the dead.

2003
02:15:13,147 --> 02:15:14,978
They can lift you up.

2004
02:15:15,227 --> 02:15:18,344
Nobody else can do that for you.
Nobody!

2005
02:15:26,787 --> 02:15:28,539
Don't you laugh at me!

2006
02:15:29,227 --> 02:15:31,502
You think you had a harsh life?

2007
02:15:31,747 --> 02:15:33,817
You got no idea.

2008
02:15:37,827 --> 02:15:40,387
Never had no bills to pay...

2009
02:15:40,707 --> 02:15:43,744
...no children to feed,
no house to clean.

2010
02:15:45,147 --> 02:15:47,138
You had it easy.

2011
02:15:49,467 --> 02:15:51,822
You can just lay there.

2012
02:16:24,307 --> 02:16:25,456
Where's Jim?

2013
02:16:42,227 --> 02:16:43,979
Thanks for dropping by.

2014
02:16:47,347 --> 02:16:51,022
I've finished my christmas party list...

2015
02:16:53,387 --> 02:16:54,297
...and you made the cut.

2016
02:16:54,547 --> 02:16:56,936
I'm honored,
but I won't be here.

2017
02:16:57,387 --> 02:16:59,457
Many will be disappointed.

2018
02:17:00,587 --> 02:17:03,021
So, obviously,
you've decided to stay in town.

2019
02:17:04,747 --> 02:17:07,625
Living here pisses off
all the right people.

2020
02:17:09,387 --> 02:17:12,504
- What can I do for you?
- I have something for you.

2021
02:17:12,747 --> 02:17:15,580
Yussopov's dagger may have seemed...

2022
02:17:15,827 --> 02:17:17,977
...more useful,
given your profession...

2023
02:17:18,227 --> 02:17:20,787
...but the painting
somehow seemed appropriate.

2024
02:17:21,027 --> 02:17:23,063
I hope you will accept it...

2025
02:17:23,307 --> 02:17:25,218
...as an expression of my gratitude.

2026
02:17:25,467 --> 02:17:27,105
<i>Newmarket Heath,</i> the overpaint.

2027
02:17:28,347 --> 02:17:29,223
Thank you.

2028
02:17:29,467 --> 02:17:31,822
I'll have it sent along.

2029
02:17:33,307 --> 02:17:35,616
I don't want to keep you
from your party.

2030
02:17:39,227 --> 02:17:42,060
But one more question, for the book.

2031
02:17:44,747 --> 02:17:46,658
Do you want to tell me
what really happened?

2032
02:17:53,107 --> 02:17:54,176
Sport...

2033
02:17:55,707 --> 02:17:57,982
...truth, like art...

2034
02:17:58,227 --> 02:18:00,138
...is in the eye of the beholder.

2035
02:18:03,227 --> 02:18:04,979
You believe what you choose...

2036
02:18:06,067 --> 02:18:07,978
...and I'll believe what I know.

2037
02:18:09,387 --> 02:18:10,661
Good luck, Jim.

2038
02:20:39,187 --> 02:20:40,540
Why didn't you come in?

2039
02:20:41,827 --> 02:20:44,341
I never enter the office on Sunday.

2040
02:20:44,587 --> 02:20:45,656
Bad juju.

2041
02:20:47,347 --> 02:20:49,065
I still got a lot of questions.

2042
02:20:51,027 --> 02:20:52,745
You know all you need to know.

2043
02:20:53,507 --> 02:20:54,781
One thing...

2044
02:20:55,187 --> 02:20:58,020
...don't commune so long with the dead
you forget the living.

2045
02:21:02,667 --> 02:21:03,941
What's this?

2046
02:21:14,987 --> 02:21:16,420
I love you, boy.

2047
02:21:17,187 --> 02:21:20,384
But I ain't the only one.
You know that, don't you?

2048
02:21:39,627 --> 02:21:41,345
How long's your lease?

2049
02:21:43,467 --> 02:21:44,866
Six months.

2050
02:21:47,267 --> 02:21:48,939
Welcome to Savannah.

2051
02:21:49,667 --> 02:21:50,543
You hungry?

2052
02:21:50,787 --> 02:21:52,698
- Come on.
- Let's go, girl.

2053
02:22:01,387 --> 02:22:04,697
You two know you're not going anywhere
without a chaperone.

2054
02:22:04,947 --> 02:22:09,225
I cooked my chablis' famous chicken.
Let's go have a picnic.

2055
02:22:10,307 --> 02:22:11,535
And guess what?

2056
02:22:11,787 --> 02:22:14,540
You get your choice of breast or thigh.

2057
02:22:15,147 --> 02:22:16,944
What's it called, the chicken?

2058
02:22:17,347 --> 02:22:19,463
Chablis' Kicking chicken.

2059
02:22:25,707 --> 02:22:27,265
Still walking the dog, Mr. Glover?

2060
02:22:27,507 --> 02:22:30,067
Yes, sir.
Patrick do like his morning walk.

2061
02:22:31,747 --> 02:22:34,978
Patrick is walking kind of fancy
this morning, isn't he?

2062
02:28:40,987 --> 02:28:42,978
Made By Chebo

